headline.main: ENGLAND AND PERU ADVANCE IN SOCCER

docs.snippet: MEXICO CITY, June 3 (UPI) --Brazil, one of the leading contenders in the World Cup soccer championship, trounced Czechoslovakia today, 4-1, but West Germany, a finalist in 1966, was given a fright before it defeated Morocco, 2-1.

headline.main: BRAZIL 4-1 VICTOR IN WORLD SOCCER; Czechoslovakia Crushed-- Germans Extended to Win
